## INTELLIGENT CONTEXT ROUTING

### When to use which knowledge file

| Situation | Load first | Process |
|-----------|------------|---------|
| **Issue / bug** | `gaps-and-risks.md` + `runbooks.md` + **`knowledge-graph.md`** (money path + edges) + relevant flow (`accounting-flows.md` / `system_brain/flows/`) | RCA: name path in graph → entry → hops → failure point → evidence → fix |
| **Multi-service / stuck async / “who should have fired?”** | **`knowledge-graph.md`** + **`cross-service-transactions.md`** + `gaps-and-risks.md` | Walk edges (ALIGNED/DRIFT/MISMATCH); check Compensation/Reconciliation row; then code |
| **Feature** | `knowledge-graph.md` (blast radius) + `orchestration-map.md` + `service-dependency-graph.md` + `platform-lib.md` | Impact: nodes/edges touched + XML + downstream services |
| **Caller / apiName inventory** | **`api-catalogue.md`** + `orchestration-map.md` | Union `apiName` / topics; grep per service |
| **Code review** | Relevant `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` for the module + `gaps-and-risks.md` (gap lenses / mining notes) | Contract, money, idempotency, txn boundaries |
| **Kafka / event** | `event-registry.md` + **`knowledge-graph.md`** (if topic is on a money path) | Topic schema + graph edge (producer → consumer → DB) |
| **Accounting edit** | `accounting-flows.md` + **`knowledge-graph.md`** (affected path) + accounting rows in `gaps-and-risks.md` | Full flow + downstream edges before edit |
| **Platform-lib edit** | `platform-lib.md` + `service-dependency-graph.md` | Blast radius across all dependent services |
| **Batch edit** | `multinode-batch.md` + `scheduler-registry.md` | Lock, idempotency, CREF determinism |
| **Schema / migration** | `accounting-flows.md` (Data Model) + schema dumps / migrations | Backward compat, NOT NULL, rollback |
| **Redis** | `redis-key-registry.md` | TTL / dedupe / lock semantics on money paths |
| **Deploy / infra** | `service-dependency-graph.md` + `config-drift-map.md` | Order, SPOF, config drift |

